{"id":"d55459cb-ddcf-4f58-8947-16a74f73acd7","title":"1513/03/11","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"ff09385e-814b-4726-a48b-9e1c9a7ea961","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"11th March. Two hours before dawn a rumour arose in Florence that the Cardinal de\u0027 Medici was Pope; and there was much bell-ringing, and bonfires were lighted in many\u00A0parts of the city, with such joy and commotion, and such persistent cries of Palle! that it made everyone get up, even the women, and go to the windows; it began at 8 in the morning (4 a.m.), by someone going about crying through the city that he had been elected; nevertheless no news had come, for on inquiring at the Palagio de\u0027 Signori and the palace of the Medici, we were told that there was no news yet. It was quite impossible, however, to do anything but cry Palle! the whole day, although nothing was known. It seemed as if the people guessed what had happened, in the most marvellous way; for it is a true proverb which says: Vox popoli, vox Dei; but to intelligent people it looked rather foolish to be ringing the bells and making bonfires before we knew the truth. ","standoffProperties":[{"id":"16bf1704-79db-4954-8413-3c90be0be403","type":"page","start":0,"end":165,"value":"266","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c741db7b-a2cb-4338-a8fc-fa17da120c78","type":"codex/time-reference","start":0,"end":9,"value":"c4c4fd84-7289-49ff-8c00-e87b3736786c","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"03cc0b9d-3efe-487c-b165-e151fd4c29e0","type":"style/superscript","start":2,"end":3,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"9d17455b-0b23-467d-be87-3e51abbe5f7b","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":49,"end":50,"value":"0c663cc2-dd9f-40ce-b17b-734e41b369ef","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d695551d-b6f7-431a-8b37-63ca99df1441","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":52,"end":59,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"8ac7e186-af6c-4d2e-8e00-a1009ecd